Henry A. SCANDRETT et al. v. Arthur ELLS, etc. No. 9132. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Sept. 18, 1939. A. N. Whitlock, A. J. Laughon, and Thos. H. Maguire, all of Seattle, Wash., and Wm. D. Keeton, of St. Maries, Idaho, for appellants. W. F. McNaughton, of Coeur d’Alene, Idaho, Therrett Towles, of Spokane, Wash., Carl M. Buell, of St. Maries, Idaho, and J. Ward Arney, of Coeur d’Alen§, Idaho, for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, HANEY, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and on motion of appellants, ordered appeal herein, 28 F.Supp. 16, dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
